node.title: 'They didn't really know what they were getting': How this country girl became a ballet star
node.description: Leanne Benjamin first took to the stage as a child in Rockhampton. With a natural talent and dedication, she became one of the Royal Ballet's most celebrated ballerinas. Now she's reliving the journey from central Queensland to Covent Garden.

node.title: 'We were left to love our daughter': Family raises $150k in two days for research into incurable disease
node.description: Tallulah Moon is one of only nine people in the world diagnosed with hereditary spastic paraplegia type 56. After initially being "crushed" by the news, her parents are fighting back by raising money to fund research into treatment and a cure.

node.title: Benedict Cumberbatch and Lady Gaga win New York Film Critics Circle awards
node.description: The critics group picks Japanese drama "Drive My Car" as year's best film; Jane Campion wins best director for "The Power of the Dog."

node.title: CBS News poll: How often do you remember your dreams?
node.description: Younger adults remember their dreams more often than older people.

node.title: Susan Rosenblatt, Who Took On Big Tobacco, Dies at 70
node.description: She was the quieter half of a law partnership with her husband that pursued a suit against cigarette companies on behalf of Florida smokers.

node.title: Chinese Developer Evergrande Says It Could Run Out of Money, Prompting Government Meetings
node.description: Evergrande's creditors expect to see a $260 million payment, but the company faces challenges coming up with the funds.

node.title: Second Grader Suspended After Allegedly Bringing Loaded Gun to Recess

node.title: Bernie Sanders Asks Biden to Prevent Medicare Premium Hike Tied to Pricey Alzheimer's Drug
node.description: The premium increase is so Medicare will have a reserve prepared if the program formally grants coverage for the drug Aduhelm, Medicare said.

node.title: Man Gets Over 6 Years in Racially Motivated Attack on Black Man, His Fourth in 7 Years

node.title: Far-Right Activist Says His Campaigning for Governor Should Count Toward Community Service

node.title: Judge Sends Man Charged in Killing of 10 at Colorado Supermarket to Mental Hospital

node.title: Comments Split on Viral TikTok Poking Fun at People Who Post Their Spotify Wrapped
node.description: "It was impulsive and it happened quickly, but it's been hilarious to see the video resonate with other people," Max Barrett of Friday Beers told Newsweek.

node.title: Fender Bender Leads to 21-Year-Old's Shooting Death in Suspected Road Rage Incident
node.description: "It appears to be road rage that escalated into a shooting that escalated into a homicide," said the Philadelphia police chief inspector on Thursday.

node.title: Record new vehicle sales for November, with ute and SUV demand strong

node.title: Phoenix coach hits out at referee's 'poor decision'

node.title: Extinction Rebellion protesters stage coal protest in Dunedin

node.title: Read the Prosecutor’s Remarks on Charging the Michigan Suspect’s Parents

node.title: ‘Essence of Rio’: Dirty Foot Bars Offer Escape From Inequality

node.title: So you want to be a backyard beekeeper. You, and many others
